-- Alterra Says Catastrophes Cost $50 Million in Fourth Quarter
-- B y   A n d r e a   L u d t k e
-- 2012-01-18T21:27:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/alterra-says-catastrophes-cost-50-million-in-fourth-quarter.html
Alterra Capital Holdings Ltd. (ALTE) , the
reinsurer formed by the merger of Max Capital Group Ltd. and
Harbor Point Ltd., said fourth-quarter catastrophe losses were
about $50 million.  The sum includes about $30 million from flooding in
 Thailand , the Bermuda-based company said today in a statement on
Business Wire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
